detaileddescription.para: Check if any of the nodes in a given avro schema is missing an ID
To have an ID for a node:

listitem.para: a field node under struct (record) schema should have FIELD_ID_PROP property
an element node under list (array) schema should have ELEMENT_ID_PROP property
a pair of key and value node under map schema should have KEY_ID_PROP and {} respectively a primitive node is not assigned any ID properties

simplesect.para: true if any of the nodes of the given Avro Schema is missing an ID property, false otherwise
